snippet.textDisplay:
Like with the new Halloween, I was so disappointed in how lazy they went. If you really think about it, Dark Fate has a lot of similarities with Terminator 3, adding a female lead, talking about Connor dying, the T-X vs REV-9, postponing Skynet vs replacing it with Legion (lazy name too), adding a new female lead.
T3 is better because it continued the canon up to Judgment Day, doing something different, which Salvation also did, Genisys litterally copied the first two but at least tried to do it differently, rebooting the franchise without litterally starting over, yet not far from it, while Dark Fate copies 1, 2 and 3 and tries to hide it, everything new doesn't make much of the movie.
Either continue on with Genisys' new timeline or continue where Salvation left off so we have a whole movie with plasma rifles
